vital_signs = ['HEARTRATE_MEAN', 'SBP_MEAN', 'DBP_MEAN',
               'MAP_MEAN', 'RR_MEAN', 'TEMP_MEAN_C', 'OXYGEN_SAT_MEAN']

for sign in vital_signs:
    print(f"\n{sign.replace('_', ' ').title()} Summary:")
    print(df[sign].describe())

    # Distribution Plot
    sns.histplot(df[sign], kde=True, bins=30, color='lightcoral')
    plt.title(f'{sign.replace("_", " ").title()} Distribution')
    plt.xlabel(sign.replace('_', ' ').title())
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.show()

    # Box Plot
    sns.boxplot(y=sign, data=df, color='lightgreen')
    plt.title(f'{sign.replace("_", " ").title()} Box Plot')
    plt.ylabel(sign.replace('_', ' ').title())
    plt.show()

In [20]:
# Convert DOD and ADMITTIME to datetime
df['DOD'] = pd.to_datetime(df['DOD'], errors='coerce')
df['ADMITTIME'] = pd.to_datetime(df['ADMITTIME'], errors='coerce')

# Calculate 30-day mortality
df['mortality_30d'] = ((df['DOD'] - df['ADMITTIME']).dt.days <= 30).astype(int)

In [26]:
# Calculate gender counts for survivors and non-survivors
survivor_gender_counts = survivors['GENDER'].value_counts()
non_survivor_gender_counts = non_survivors['GENDER'].value_counts()

# Print the results
print("Survivors Gender Counts:")
print(survivor_gender_counts)

print("\nNon-Survivors Gender Counts:")
print(non_survivor_gender_counts)

# Create a DataFrame for visualization
gender_count_df = pd.DataFrame({
    'Survivors': survivor_gender_counts,
    'Non-Survivors': non_survivor_gender_counts
}).T  # Transpose for easier plotting

# Define custom colors: blue for 'M' and pink for 'F'
custom_colors = ['blue', 'pink']  # Assuming columns are ordered as ['M', 'F']

# Plot the grouped bar chart
ax = gender_count_df.plot(
    kind='bar',
    figsize=(8, 6),
    color=custom_colors,
    edgecolor='black'
)

# Add title and labels
plt.title('Gender Counts: Survivors vs. Non-Survivors', fontsize=14)
plt.xlabel('Group', fontsize=12)
plt.ylabel('Count', fontsize=12)
plt.xticks(rotation=0)
plt.legend(title='Gender', labels=['Male', 'Female'])
plt.grid(axis='y', linestyle='--', alpha=0.7)

# Add count labels on top of the bars
for container in ax.containers:
    ax.bar_label(container, label_type='edge', fontsize=10)

# Show the plot
plt.show()
